uot; were two major features of Luclin, as well as the bazaar code for letting players act as vendors in certain trade zones.<br>
<br>
Let's see, December 4th was the release of Luclin.  Many bugs with Umbra STILL have yet to be fixed.<br>
<br>
It's June 17th, still no bazaar code, no new interface, focus items still not fully implemented.<br>
<br>
They also said that equipment should be a way to distinguish players of a given class and level.  In what way is this done when all focus items of a given type have identical effects?  Is a 20 percent max improvement to damage item different from another 20 percent max improvement on another?  Oh, one has better stats than the other, but stats, and even mana pool only affect manaburn, so how does the current implementation distinguish one level 60 with sunstrike from another when the DPS is identical?<br>
<br>
Yes, I agree, focus items are an improvement for us, but they almost seem to have been an afterthought, as if they were working on PoP, then the boss asks during an evaluation, &quot;So, you said you'd have focus effects done by December 4th.  Can you get them done before June 1st?&quot;  Then a few days before the deadline, the person realized, &quot;I'm in trouble, I have no progress on the project, I'd better get SOMETHING done on it, or I'll be fired&quot;.<br>
<br>
That's how it seems to be, that a threat needed to be made by a manager, and a few days before the deadline, the work was only partially done, just enough to avoid being fired.  <br>
 <p>Targonis Manastorm<br>
Level 60 Wizard<br>
The First Seal<br>
The Nameless Server<br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/udonisdragori.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DonisDragori</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/17/02 11:24:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=17235.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Game Just Got Much Better for us Casters!</span><hr size=1> Concerning focus items I think they used a grab bag approach.  List 200 items usuable by all casters, /random 1 200 for effect A.  Then move to effect B and so on.  Rinse and repeat until Boss is satisfied with the numbers.<br>
<br>
Donis <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/udaynan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Daynan</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.flagaustnat.asn.au/images/flagcurrent.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/18/02 1:12:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=17235.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Game Just Got Much Better for us Casters!</span><hr size=1> My main is a 60 cleric. <br>
<br>
I only recently started playing my wizard. I had him at level 6 and in the EC tunnel as a mule for about 6 months prior to leveling him up. During those 6 months any caster gear I came across I just put it aside for him. When I started playing him he had about 200-ish  int and 200 mana. I was surprised how easy it was to get this much with items.<br>
<br>
From level 6 to 24 I grouped with others less than a dozen times and since then ( I am 45 now ) I have barely grouped at all spending most of my time soloing. When soloing mana preservation and improved damage items are great. They make a slight improvement on the rate at which I can kill mobs. Improved damage usually only saves me the Fire Bolt or 2 needed to finish off a mob. I use Fire Bolt still because I like the effect when the mob dies <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
The amount of times I have grouped have been rare and so I don't think I can consider myself an expert on wizard grouping. However the times I have grouped I  have felt myself to be inneficient. Sure this is just a feeling I haven't done a serious evaluation of it, but when I have to restrict myself to a max 2 nukes per pull to conserve mana and each nuke moves the mobs hp 1/8th of the way down (1/4 total  damage) I don't feel like I am pulling my own weight. I am sure that in the same situation if I was a melee character I would have done approx. equal damage to the MT. Partial/full resists make this situation worse.<br>
<br>
The problem as I see it is that we are restricted by our mana supply in such situations and our current mana supplies can not keep up with the centi longswords selling for 200pp in the EC tunnel. Those long swords can keep swinging as long as the bearers have hp.<br>
<br>
The focus items are a great start to address balance issues but it should be considered as only a beginning not as a complete fix.<br>
<br>
As a cleric if I cast 1 spell per fight (complete heal @ 400mana) I have done my part and I am a productive and desirable member of the group.  Unforetunatly clerics are considered &quot;balanced&quot; because of this 1 spell but that's another argument. You'll notice I'm playing a wizard now anyway.<br>
<br>
In another caster balance post someone mentioned that wizards need more right click dd items of a calibre similar to the JBB for shamans in order to keep up with melee damage over the long haul. It would be great if such items were added for use during the lower levels but I doubt it will happen.<br>
<br>
Here are some more suggestions I doubt will ever happen.<br>
<br>
Add a variety of Improved Damage effects to wiz only items.<br>
eg<br>
- 5%-15%<br>
- 10%-20%<br>
- 15%-20%<br>
- 10%-30%<br>
Melee's get a choice of FBSS or CoF why can't wizards get the same? The ability to upgrade your gear is part of what makes the game fun.<br>
<br>
Also.<br>
<br>
A lure type nuke that works in a manner similar to harvest. get it at level 30 (when most people should be grouping).<br>
It should have a 10 second cast time time and 10 second stun time so it can't be abused for soloing. I'm guessing an approximate 3 minutes recast time so it can be used in chain pulling groups. 1 mana to cast with damage scaling up with each level. I'm thinking it should do about 500 damage at level 44 (conflagration does 606) and it should go up by about 40 hp per level for a total of about 1100-1200 at level 60.<br>
<br>
I believe that if a wiz can do at least this much damage per mob even while oom they will be closer to being balanced with melee.<br>
<br>
For now I'll go back to soloing.<br>
<br>
